<HEADLINE> Couple arraigned for second-degree murder  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NORWICH, N.Y. (AP) - Charged with the second-degree murder, a
Staten Island man and his fiancee were arraigned and sent to the
Chenango County Correctional Facility.
</P>
<P>
   Xavier Lee Valentine, 38, and Joanne Carroll, 34, were arraigned
before Town of Norwich Justice David Evans Sunday for the shotgun
shooting of Edward Pastore Jr.
</P>
<P>
   Pastore, 22, from the Town of Norwich, was shot and killed early
July 17 during a home-invasion robbery, police said. His two
roommates were not injured.
</P>
<P>
   Valentine, also known as ''Midnight,'' and Carroll, also known
as Joanne L. Baqrile, were sent to the Chenango County Correctional
Facility without bail, pending further legal action. Their
arraignment took only four minutes, with both requesting
court-appointed attorneys.
</P>
<P>
   The two were arrested Saturday in Staten Island by members of
the state police assigned to Troop C, the Troop New York City Drug
Enforcement Task Force, and the New York City Police Department.
</P>
</TEXT>
