<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canandaigua man charged with death of mother  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   CANANDAIGUA, N.Y. (AP) - A 38-year-old man was held without bail
in Ontario County jail for the second-degree murder of his
57-year-old mother.
</P>
<P>
   Ontario County District Attorney R. Michael Tantillo said other
charges against Jerald O. Zimmerman, 38, were likely - such as
those stemming from Jerald's alleged attack on his father at the
home.
</P>
<P>
   According to police, authorities were called Sunday morning
because of a domestic dispute. There, they found Angela Mae
Zimmerman dead on the dining room floor.
</P>
<P>
   Her body was taken to the Monroe County Medical Examiner's
Office for an autopsy. Tantillo said she appears to have died of a
beating.
</P>
<P>
   Zimmerman's death is the city's first slaying since 1991,
according to Canandaigua police.
</P>
<P>
   No motive has been determined, police said.
</P>
</TEXT>
