<HEADLINE> Dow Climbs 10; Nasdaq Gains 30  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up ten
points in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York
Stock Exchange hold a 7-4 lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 30 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is up five points.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street appears in the mood to do some early
bargain-hunting.
</P>
<P>
   The question is whether there's enough interest to sustain the
market's early gains.
</P>
<P>
   Some analysts say we could see the popular averages suffer
through a few more weeks of declines.
</P>
<P>
   Certainly, there's little in the way of market-moving news to
help give Wall Street support today.
</P>
<P>
   The earnings news has slowed dramatically from last week, and
there won't be any key economic news until tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
   What there is, however, is the realization that the Nasdaq
composite fell more than ten percent last week alone.
</P>
