<HEADLINE> Christina Aguilera Fans Dig in Beans  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   KEARNEY, Neb. (AP) -- Forget the genie. These Christina Aguilera
fans were looking for tickets in a bottle.
</P>
<P>
   At the Hilltop Mall on Saturday, 30 contestants lined up to dig
their way through a tub with 100 pounds of pork and beans in search
of a pair of tickets to a local concert by the teen pop singer.
</P>
<P>
   Thirty bottles were buried somewhere in the beans. Half of them
contained a pair of tickets to Thursday's concert at the Buffalo
County Fair.
</P>
<P>
   It was about the only choice for the fans of Aguilera, whose
debut single ''Genie In A Bottle'' reached No. 1. All 5,800 tickets
for the show have sold out.
</P>
