<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-31 15:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 69; Nasdaq Adds 85  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks rebounded Monday as bargain hunters
returned to the market following last week's big decline.
Technology stocks led the resurgence.
</P>
<P>
   But investors remained uneasy about corporate profits and
inflation, a combination that caused stocks to tumble on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   At late afternoon on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average was up 68.59 at 10,580.34. The Dow lost nearly 75 points
Friday and was down 2 percent last week.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq was up 84.84 at 3,739.49 Monday after dropping more
than 10 percent last week. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 Index was up
14.27 at 1,434.28
</P>
<P>
   ''I think this is a reaction to last week's selloff,'' said
Barry Berman, head trader for Robert W. Baird &AMP; Co in Milwaukee.
</P>
<P>
   He said investors remain nervous about inflation and whether
Federal Reserve policymakers later this month will implement their
seventh interest rate hike since June 1999.
</P>
<P>
   ''Up until last week it was pretty much assumed the Fed would
not do anything. But now that is in question,'' Berman said.
</P>
<P>
   The markets were still already nervous about higher rates before
Friday's stronger-than-expected report on the second-quarter gross
domestic product intensified inflation fears and led to renewed
selling. To get a better idea of where the economy and inflation
stand, investors will be closely be watching reports this week on
consumer spending, new home sales, manufacturing and retail sales.
</P>
<P>
   Leading the Dow higher Monday was Hewlett Packard, up $4.50 at
$111.50 and American Express, up $1.312 at $57.125.
</P>
<P>
   Chip makers and Internet and computer companies were lifting the
Nasdaq. Those included Texas Instruments, up $2 at $59.50, Oracle,
up $2.50 at $74.75 and eBay, up $2 at $48.875.
</P>
<P>
   VISX, the laser vision system maker that has used in surgery on
Tiger Woods and other celebrities, rose $2.813 to $24.813 after
reports that financier Carl Icahn plans to acquire an 11 percent
stake in the company.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index was up 4.30 at 494.52.
</P>
<P>
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 7-to-5 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 675.54 million
shares, down from Friday's pace.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   New York Stock Exchange: http://www.nyse.com
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Stock Market: http://www.nasdaq.com
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
