<HEADLINE> BC-NY--Job Count Investigation, 2nd Ld-Writethru,0805  </HEADLINE>
By ANNY KUO
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - The federal government is investigating New
York state's robust 1999 job-growth numbers following complaints
that the statistics might have been inflated.
</P>
<P>
   In March, the state revised its 1999 job-growth rate from the
original estimate of 1.8 percent to 2.6 percent, an increase that
''looked a little bit unusual,'' said Patricia Getz, division chief
for monthly industrial employment statistics at the federal Bureau
of Labor Statistics.
</P>
<P>
   ''The revisions for New York was larger than what we usually
see,'' Getz said Monday. ''We're just trying to make sure there are
