<HEADLINE> Gifford Farewell Gets Big Ratings  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Regis Philbin may have lost his 15-year co-host
last week, but he got hefty ratings in return.
</P>
<P>
   Last Friday's ''Live with Regis &AMP; Kathie Lee'' farewell for
Kathie Lee Gifford earned a robust 10.4 household rating and 33
share, according to preliminary ratings that measure roughly
one-half of the nation.
</P>
<P>
   Released Monday by Buena Vista Television, which syndicates the
daytime talk show, the figures indicate that one-third of all
people watching TV tuned in to see Gifford bid goodbye to her fans
and Philbin. That represents an estimated 7 million viewers
overall, compared with a typical audience of 4.1 million.
</P>
<P>
   The full farewell week scored a 77 percent increase in audience
share over the same period a year ago.
</P>
<P>
   Philbin is carrying on in Gifford's absence, with a search for a
new permanent co-host under way.
</P>
