<HEADLINE> By The Associated Press  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Tuesday will continue warm and sticky over most areas
of upstate
New York, but there may be breaks of sunshine. There's a chance of
showers and thunderstorms late in the day. Daytime highs will be in
the lower 80s, nighttime lows will be near 70.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Wednesday will bring occasional sunshine with a 40 percent
chance of afternoon thunderstorms, the National Weather Service
says. Daytime highs will be in the lower 80s, nighttime lows will
be in the upper 60s.
</P>
<P>
   Showers and thunderstorms are likely Thursday. Highs will be in
the mid 70s.
</P>
</TEXT>
